Version Beta 0.9.3
=====
Fix: bug in cmd_upgrade_all , thanks to conraid again!
- THE BUG (reported live by conraid, reproduced on thinkstar1)
------------------------------------------------------------
`upgrade-all` filtered frozen packages by testing the blacklist against the
INSTALLED id only (bl_installed on u.installed). A date/version rule such as
`xf86-.*-202.*` only ever matches the INCOMING build (e.g.
xf86-input-evdev-20260421_...), never the older installed one (2.11.0), so the
very build the user froze was offered for upgrade. Meanwhile `info` (which tests
bl_frozen on each candidate) correctly showed it [blacklisted] — the visible
inconsistency.

THE FIX (src/main.rs, cmd_upgrade_all)
--------------------------------------
Filter with bl_frozen(cfg, &db, &installed, u.available) — the candidate-aware
check every other path already uses (upgrade <pattern>, install, install-new,
reinstall, info, add_with_deps). It covers both the candidate and any
@repo-scoped rule on the installed source, so nothing the old installed-only
test caught is lost. Frozen names are now collected and reported via
note_frozen_excluded(), so the user sees "frozen (skipped)" instead of a silent
drop. One change, one function. No behaviour change for remove/clean-system
(those correctly stay installed-only — there is no candidate in a removal).
